function [m,v,q50]=loggaussstat(param);% loggaussstat              - Mean, variance and median of the log-Gaussian distribution (Jan 1,2001)%% Return the mean, variance and median for a log-Gaussian% distribution with specified mean and variance parameters% for the associated Gaussian distribution.%% SYNTAX :%% [m,v,q50]=loggaussstat(param);%% INPUT :%% param    1 by 2   parameters of the Gaussian distribution, where :%                   param(1) is the mean of the distribution,%                   param(2) is the variance of the distribution.%% OUTPUT :%% m        scalar   mean of the distribution.% v        scalar   variance of the distribution.% q50      scalar   mediane of the distribution.mGauss=param(1);vGauss=param(2);w=exp(vGauss);m=exp(0.5*vGauss+mGauss);v=(exp(mGauss)^2)*w*(w-1);q50=loggaussinv(0.5,[mGauss vGauss]);